[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man dies in Ayrshire after being struck by car

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An 18-year-old man has died after being struck by a car while walking along a main road in Ayrshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The accident happened at about 22:40 on Friday on the A77 Glasgow to Stranraer road close to the Bellfield interchange, east of Kilmarnock.
James Watson, from Kilmarnock, was hit by a Fiat Punto. He was pronounced dead at the scene.
The 28-year-old driver was uninjured but was taken to Crosshouse Hospital for treatment for shock.
Police closed the road for about four hours, and appealed for any witnesses to contact them.
